Adds Spotify functionality into MuSicX's existing screens using tiny,
guarded injection points. Each hook is a self-contained new file that
MuSicX's shared screens call with a single line — never touching the
existing YouTube/local logic.

Hook 1 (HomeScreen): SpotifyHomeInjector renders Spotify home sections
    at the top of HomeScreen's LazyColumn. Backed by new
    SpotifyHomeViewModel (separate from HomeViewModel to avoid conflicts).
    Guarded by EnableSpotifyKey + UseSpotifyHomeKey + logged-in.

Hook 2 (LibraryPlaylistsScreen): SpotifyLibraryInjector renders the user's
    Spotify playlists + folders at the top of the library playlists list.
    Guarded by EnableSpotifyKey + logged-in.

Hook 3 (SongMenu + PlayerMenu): 'Add to Spotify Playlist' action added to
    the NewActionGrid. Resolves Spotify URI from spotify_match table.
    Uses new SpotifyAddToPlaylistDialog helper. Action hidden when
    Spotify disabled (via .takeIf { ... } on the list entry).

Hook 4 (OnlineSearchResult): SpotifySearchInjector renders Spotify search
    results above YouTube results when Spotify is enabled + UseSpotifySearch
    + user is logged in. Includes playlists, albums, and tracks.

Hook 5 (MusicService Spotify URI dispatch): NO CODE NEEDED — the existing
    playerConnection.playQueue(queue) polymorphism already accepts
    SpotifyPlaylistQueue and SpotifyLikedSongsQueue as Queue subtypes,
    and Spotify screens instantiate them directly.

Hook 6 (Artist/Album Spotify equivalents): SpotifyEquivalentInjector
    adds 'Open on Spotify' button on AlbumScreen and ArtistScreen when
    a Spotify match exists for a seed song. Opens the Spotify web URL
    via ACTION_VIEW intent — works with app or browser.

New files:
